b'Biography'
b'Hulya Seferoglu is an Assistant Professor in the Electrical and Computer Engineering Department of University of Illinois at Chicago. Before joining University of Illinois at Chicago, she was a Postdoctoral Associate at Massachusetts Institute of Technology. She received her Ph.D. degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from University of California, Irvine, M.S. degree in Electrical Engineering and  Computer Science from Sabanci University, and B.S. degree in Electrical Engineering from Istanbul University. She worked as a summer intern in AT&T  Labs Research, Docomo USA Labs, and Microsoft Research, Cambridge.   '
